Zagrebacka Banka Shareholders Pass Five-for-One Stock Split

-- B y   J a s m i n a   K u z m a n o v i c
-- 
2011-07-26T14:35:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-22/croatia-stocks-drop-most-in-2-years-as-zagrebacka-banka-plunges.html
Shareholders of Zagrebacka Banka
d.d., the Croatian unit of  Italy ’s  UniCredit SpA (UCG) , approved a
five-for-one stock split, the bank said today in a statement to
the Zagreb stock exchange.  The shareholders decided to increase the company’s capital
using its retained earnings by 5.1 billion kuna ($990 million)
to 6.4 billion kuna, it said.. The bank will issue 256 million
new shares to reach the total of 320 million shares, each with a
nominal value of 20 kuna.  Each shareholder will be able to subscribe four new shares
for every share they currently own. To be eligible for the
split, shareholders must be registered on today’s date.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jasmina Kuzmanovic at 
 jkuzmanovic@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  